{
  "doc_id": "61472",
  "text": "HINT1 is a novel tumor inhibiter identified in recent years [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . It is implicated in the pathological progression of a number of human diseases, including cancer and schizophrenia [CITATION_3] . Wu et al [CITATION_4] found that rhHint1 was capable of attenuating CCl 4 -induced liver fibrosis in rats by simultaneously targeting multiple pathogenic pathways, and may have potential for development as a novel treatment for liver fibrosis. The present study demonstrated that the level of HINT1 autoantibody in patients with HBV-related liver cirrhosis was higher than that in patients with CHB. However, further studies on the mechanism underlying the generation of HINT1 autoantibody are required.",
